cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.CG, cs.DM 

This paper is about a programming tactic involving polyhedra that has been widely applied in the polyhedral analysis of (constraint) logic programs. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the programming languages (cs.PL) or data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves computations of convex hulls, which suggests that it may also belong to the computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. The use of linear constraint solving machinery suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or discrete mathematics (cs.DM) sub-categories.
